messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Files:
- app/Http/Controllers/PostCommentController.php

Explanation:
- The route Route::resource('posts.comments', PostCommentController::class)->only('index'); in routes/web.php refers to the class App\Http\Controllers\PostCommentController.
- The implementation of the index method for that exact class is in app/Http/Controllers/PostCommentController.php. Its index(Post $post) returns the comments view with the post's comments (eager-loading the author and ordering by latest).
- Note: there is another controller with a similar name at app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostCommentController.php (namespace App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1). That file also defines an index method, but it is a different fully-qualified class and is not the controller referenced by routes/web.php.
